  RFC4998 [label="RFC4998
Evidence Record Syntax (ERS)
2007", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="In many scenarios, users must be able prove the existence and integrity of data, including digitally signed data, in a common and reproducible way over a long and possibly undetermined period of time.  This document specifies the syntax and processing of an Evidence Record, a structure designed to support long-term non-repudiation of existence of data. [STANDARDS-TRACK]", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

